<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-04-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-04-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="342" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d342">
                    <head>Inhabitants of Dublin</head>
                    <dateline>35 <hi rend="smallcaps">Molesworth Street</hi>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-04-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 28, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                    <p rend="flushleft">
                        <hi rend="italic">To the right honorable the Lord Mayor:</hi>
                    </p>
                    <p>We, the undersigned, citizens of Dublin, request your lordship to convene a
                        public meeting, at your very earliest convenience, to express our
                        indignation and sorrow at the assassination of President Lincoln, and our
                        sympathy with the people of the United States.</p>
                    <p>The above was signed by Joseph Wilson, D. L., and 426 other names and
                        firms.</p>
                    <postscript>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Mansion House</hi>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-04-28">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 28, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>In compliance with the above influentially-signed request, I hereby
                            convene a meeting of the citizens of Dublin, to be held in Oak Room
                            Mansion House, on to-morrow, Saturday, April 29, at 2 o’clock.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>JOHN BARRINGTON, </signed>
                            <hi rend="italic">Lord Mayor</hi>.</closer>
                    </postscript>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>